@startuml
title Edge Computing Platform for Deep Learning - Model Deployment Control Flow

actor User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Flask Backend\n(main_service.py)" as Backend
participant "MySQL Database" as DB
participant "Google Cloud Storage" as GCS
participant "Cloud Function\n(TFLite Converter)" as CloudFunc
participant "Model Manager\n(Go Service)" as ModelMgr
participant "Kubernetes API" as K8s
participant "KubeEdge" as Edge
participant "TensorRT/TFLite\nInference Service" as Inference

== User Registration & Authentication ==
User -> Frontend: Register/Login
Frontend -> Backend: POST /user/register or /login
Backend -> DB: Store/Validate User Credentials
DB --> Backend: User Data
Backend --> Frontend: Authentication Token
Frontend --> User: Login Success

== Project Creation ==
User -> Frontend: Create New Project
Frontend -> Backend: POST /project/create
Backend -> DB: Create Project Entry\n(associate with user)
DB --> Backend: Project ID
Backend -> ModelMgr: Create Namespace & ServiceAccount
ModelMgr -> K8s: kubectl create namespace\nkubectl create serviceaccount
K8s --> ModelMgr: Namespace Created
ModelMgr --> Backend: Resource Created
Backend --> Frontend: Project Created
Frontend --> User: Project Ready

== Model Upload & Conversion ==
User -> Frontend: Upload TensorFlow SavedModel
Frontend -> Backend: POST /model/upload
Backend -> GCS: Upload Model to Bucket
GCS --> Backend: Model URL
Backend -> DB: Store Model Metadata\n(project_id, model_path)
DB --> Backend: Model Record Created
Backend -> CloudFunc: Trigger TFLite Conversion\n(model_path)
activate CloudFunc
CloudFunc -> GCS: Download SavedModel
GCS --> CloudFunc: Model Files
CloudFunc -> CloudFunc: Convert to TFLite
CloudFunc -> GCS: Upload TFLite Model
GCS --> CloudFunc: TFLite Model URL
CloudFunc --> Backend: Conversion Complete
deactivate CloudFunc
Backend -> DB: Update Model Status\n(tflite_path)
DB --> Backend: Updated
Backend --> Frontend: Model Ready for Deployment
Frontend --> User: Model Converted

== Model Deployment to Edge ==
User -> Frontend: Deploy Model to Edge
Frontend -> Backend: POST /model/deploy\n(model_id, target_nodes)
Backend -> DB: Get Model & Project Info
DB --> Backend: Model Metadata
Backend -> ModelMgr: Deploy Model Request\n(namespace, model_path, replicas)
activate ModelMgr
ModelMgr -> K8s: Create ConfigMap\n(model configuration)
K8s --> ModelMgr: ConfigMap Created
ModelMgr -> K8s: Create Deployment\n(TFLite/TensorRT container)
K8s --> ModelMgr: Deployment Created
ModelMgr -> K8s: Create Service\n(expose inference endpoint)
K8s --> ModelMgr: Service Created
ModelMgr -> K8s: Label Nodes for Edge\n(node affinity rules)
K8s --> ModelMgr: Nodes Labeled
K8s -> Edge: Sync Deployment to Edge Nodes
Edge -> Edge: Pull Container Image
Edge -> Edge: Start Inference Service
Edge --> K8s: Pod Running Status
K8s --> ModelMgr: Deployment Status
deactivate ModelMgr
ModelMgr --> Backend: Deployment Successful
Backend -> DB: Update Deployment Status
DB --> Backend: Updated
Backend --> Frontend: Deployment Complete
Frontend --> User: Model Deployed

== Inference Request ==
User -> Frontend: Upload Image for Inference
Frontend -> Backend: POST /inference/upload
Backend -> GCS: Upload Inference Input
GCS --> Backend: Input URL
Backend -> DB: Store Inference Request
DB --> Backend: Request ID
Backend -> Inference: HTTP POST /predict\n(input_url)
activate Inference
Inference -> GCS: Download Input Data
GCS --> Inference: Input Image
Inference -> Inference: Preprocess Image
Inference -> Inference: TensorRT/TFLite Inference\n(object detection)
Inference -> Inference: Postprocess Results\n(NMS, bounding boxes)
Inference --> Backend: Inference Results\n(detected objects, scores)
deactivate Inference
Backend -> GCS: Store Results
GCS --> Backend: Results URL
Backend -> DB: Update Inference Record
DB --> Backend: Updated
Backend --> Frontend: Inference Complete
Frontend --> User: Display Results\n(bounding boxes, labels)

== Cluster Status Monitoring ==
User -> Frontend: View Cluster Status
Frontend -> Backend: GET /cluster/status
Backend -> ModelMgr: Get Cluster Info
ModelMgr -> K8s: kubectl get nodes\nkubectl get pods
K8s --> ModelMgr: Cluster State
ModelMgr -> Edge: Get Edge Node Status
Edge --> ModelMgr: Edge Node State
ModelMgr --> Backend: Cluster Status\n(nodes, pods, resources)
Backend --> Frontend: Status Data
Frontend --> User: Display Dashboard

== Model Scaling ==
User -> Frontend: Scale Model Replicas
Frontend -> Backend: POST /model/scale\n(model_id, replicas)
Backend -> ModelMgr: Scale Deployment\n(namespace, deployment, replicas)
ModelMgr -> K8s: kubectl scale deployment
K8s -> Edge: Update Replica Count
Edge -> Edge: Start/Stop Pods
Edge --> K8s: Scaling Complete
K8s --> ModelMgr: Deployment Scaled
ModelMgr --> Backend: Scaling Successful
Backend -> DB: Update Deployment Config
DB --> Backend: Updated
Backend --> Frontend: Scaling Complete
Frontend --> User: Replicas Updated

@enduml
